The White House hosted a National Conference on Mental Health to increase understanding and awareness about mental health. The conference brought together mental health advocates, educators, healthcare providers, faith leaders, members of Congress, representatives from local governments, and individuals who have struggled with mental health problems. The conference aimed to reduce stigma and help those struggling with mental health problems recognize the importance of reaching out for assistance. The conference built on the President's plan to reduce gun violence and included steps to expand mental health coverage, support young people, and improve access to services for veterans. The conference also highlighted commitments made by various organizations to increase understanding and awareness of mental health. The event included panel discussions, presentations, and networking opportunities to encourage collaboration.